from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor

In [4]:
df['job_grouped'] = df['job_title'].replace(title_mapping)
In [5]:
df_filtered = df[df['job_grouped'].isin(['Data Scientist', 'Data Engineer', 'Machine Learning Engineer', 'Data Analyst'])]

In [7]:
Y = df_filtered['salary_in_usd']
X = df_filtered[['job_grouped', 'experience_level', 'company_size', 'remote_ratio', 'company_location', 'work_year']]
In [8]:
categorical_features = ['job_grouped', 'experience_level', 'company_size', 'company_location']

preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(
    transformers=[
        ('step_1', OneHotEncoder(drop='first', handle_unknown='ignore'), categorical_features)
    ],
    remainder='passthrough'
)
In [9]:
X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test = train_test_split(
    X, Y, test_size=0.2, random_state = 42
)
In [10]:
model = Pipeline([
    ('preprocessor', preprocessor),
    ('regression', LinearRegression())
])

model.fit(X_train, Y_train)
Out[10]:
Pipeline(steps=[('preprocessor',
                 ColumnTransformer(remainder='passthrough',
                                   transformers=[('step_1',
                                                  OneHotEncoder(drop='first',
                                                                handle_unknown='ignore'),
                                                  ['job_grouped',
                                                   'experience_level',
                                                   'company_size',
                                                   'company_location'])])),
                ('regression', LinearRegression())])
In [11]:
Y_pred = model.predict(X_test)

print("MAE:", round(mean_absolute_error(Y_test, Y_pred), 2))
print("RMSE:", round(mean_squared_error(Y_test, Y_pred, squared=False), 2))
print("R² Score:", round(r2_score(Y_test, Y_pred), 3))

    ('preprocessor', preprocessor),  # Reuse your existing preprocessor
    ('regression', RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42))
])

In [32]:
encoded_cols = rf_model.named_steps['preprocessor']\
    .named_transformers_['step_1']\
    .get_feature_names_out(categorical_features)

passthrough_cols = ['remote_ratio', 'work_year'] 
all_features = np.concatenate([encoded_cols, passthrough_cols])
In [33]:
importances = rf_model.named_steps['regression'].feature_importances_

# Sort the features by importance
indices = np.argsort(importances)[::-1]
sorted_features = [all_features[i] for i in indices]
sorted_importances = importances[indices]
